SIMPLE: girl
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Girl
<hw>Girl</hw> <pr>(g⟦etil⟧rl)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>girle</ets>, <ets>gerle</ets>, <ets>gurle</ets>, a girl (in sense
1): cf. LG. <ets>g⟦oum⟧r</ets> child.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A young person of either sex; a child.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A female child, from birth to the age of puberty; a
young maiden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A female servant; a maidservant.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A roebuck two years old.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>girlfriend</ent>⟦br⟧
